  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Community Resilience and Social Cohesion amongst Select Border Communities in Northern Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall purpose of this programme is to utilize a human security approach that is people-centred, context-specific, comprehensive and preventative, to contribute towards enhancing border community resilience and social cohesion amongst three select border communities in the northern part of the Republic of Ghana: Namoo, Pulimakom and Missiga Pusiga.</narrative>
  </description>
